When encountering a post that seems dubious, I use the platform’s built‑in tools—reporting and flagging options—to alert moderators. Most social media companies have policies against fake news, and reporting increases the likelihood that such content will be reviewed or removed. Additionally, I curate my feed by unfollowing accounts that frequently spread falsehoods, thereby creating a healthier information ecosystem around me.

